      {
        "id": 3930936,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-11-13T16:55:52.179Z",
        "cooked": "<p>My bad, guys! Seems that either Guffens misspoke or I mis-wrote when writing my notes from barrel/tank on the unbottled 2019s (tasted alongside the bottled 18s, when a 1er Jus des Hauts des Vignes was produced), and that I perpetuated the error when reviewing the (unlabelled) bottled wines.</p>\n<p>It doesn\u2019t change the wine in the bottle, however: it\u2019s the first press juice (lowest pH) from Guffens\u2019 best holdings in Pouilly-Fuiss\u00e9, which were all blended together given the small yield (so it has the likes of Petits Croux, Croux and La Roche in it). The later press fractions were used to make Guffens\u2019 one-off Triangle bottling.</p>\n<p>Will get that amended in our database presently.</p>",
